Name: Aett
Description: This rune symbolizes the words from a noble's mouth, the speech of a leader, the silvertongue of a merchant. It grants those who channel it greater charm and influence.
Types: Rune, Basic, Lesser, Greater, Epic
Basic Rune: Requires having succeeded on a contested Charisma check to convince a hostile creature that you are no threat to it during active combat to attune. This rune symbolizes the words from a noble's mouth, the speech of a leader, the silvertongue of a merchant. It grants those who channel it greater charm and influence.SPACESPACESilvered TongueSPACEAs an action, you speak honeyed words of deception and illusion. Choose a creature within DISTANCE15-45DISTANCE feet of you that can hear you. The target must make a Wisdom saving throw, and does so with advantage if you or your companions are fighting it. On a failed save, the target becomes charmed by you for TIME1-5TIME minutes or until you or your companions do anything harmful to it. When this effect ends, the creature is unaware that it was charmed by you. A creature that succeeds on its saving throw is immune to this effect for the next 24 hours.SPACESPACEYou may invoke this rune a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus before its magic is deplted. The rune will recharge from ambient magic as you complete a long rest. This rune occupies 1 runic attunement slot. 
